('Dementia with Lewy Bodies (DLB)', 'Cholinesterase inhibitor (Donepezil, Rivastigmine). Extreme caution with antipsychotics (high risk of severe sensitivity reaction). Treat associated Parkinsonism (Levodopa cautiously). Manage REM sleep behavior disorder (Clonazepam).', 'Typical Antipsychotics', 'Rivastigmine patch daily, Clonazepam QHS', 'Clinical diagnosis based on fluctuating cognition, visual hallucinations, Parkinsonism', 'Requires careful medication management due to sensitivities.'),
('Acute Appendicitis', 'Surgical consult for appendectomy (usually laparoscopic). NPO, IV fluids, IV antibiotics (covering gram negatives/anaerobes, e.g., Cefoxitin or Pip/Tazo). Pain control.', 'NKDA', 'IV Normal Saline, IV Cefoxitin, IV Morphine PRN', 'CT Abdomen: Appendiceal wall thickening, periappendiceal fat stranding', 'Patient admitted with RLQ pain, anorexia, fever, leukocytosis.'),
('Sickle Cell Disease - Acute Chest Syndrome', 'Admission. Oxygen therapy. IV fluids (careful monitoring). Pain control. Empiric antibiotics (Ceftriaxone + Azithromycin). Consider exchange transfusion if severe.', 'NKDA', 'Oxygen via NC, IV Fluids, IV PCA, IV Ceftriaxone, IV Azithromycin', 'Chest X-ray: New infiltrate. Patient hypoxic with chest pain/fever.', 'Serious complication requiring prompt treatment.'),
('Age-Related Macular Degeneration, Wet (Neovascular AMD)', 'Intravitreal injections of Anti-VEGF agents (e.g., Ranibizumab, Aflibercept, Bevacizumab). Monitor vision and OCT scans regularly.', 'NKDA', 'Intravitreal Aflibercept injection monthly (initially)', 'Ophthalmology Exam/OCT: Subretinal fluid/hemorrhage noted', 'Requires ongoing treatment by Retina specialist to preserve vision.'),
('Glaucoma, Angle Closure - Acute Attack', 'Emergency! Immediate IOP lowering (IV Acetazolamide, Mannitol, topical beta-blockers/alpha-agonists/miotics). Laser peripheral iridotomy definitive treatment once IOP controlled.', 'Sulfa (caution with Acetazolamide)', 'IV Acetazolamide, Timolol/Pilocarpine eye drops STAT', 'IOP >50 mmHg. Exam: Mid-dilated fixed pupil, corneal edema, shallow anterior chamber', 'Ophthalmology emergency consult obtained.'),
('Inflammatory Bowel Disease (Ulcerative Colitis) - Moderate Flare', 'Increase dose of 5-ASA agent (Mesalamine). Add oral Prednisone taper. Consider adding Azathioprine or biologic therapy if frequent flares.', 'NKDA', 'Mesalamine DR 1.2g PO TID, Prednisone 40mg daily with taper', 'Sigmoidoscopy: Active inflammation, ulcerations. Fecal calprotectin elevated.', 'Patient reports increased bloody diarrhea, urgency, abdominal pain.'),
('Bacterial Meningitis', 'Empiric IV antibiotics STAT (e.g., Ceftriaxone + Vancomycin +/- Ampicillin if Listeria risk). Dexamethasone prior to/with first antibiotic dose. Lumbar puncture for CSF analysis/culture. Droplet precautions.', 'Penicillin (Anaphylaxis)', 'IV Meropenem + Vancomycin, IV Dexamethasone', 'LP: High WBC (neutrophils), high protein, low glucose. Gram stain pending.', 'Medical emergency requiring immediate treatment.'),
('Suicidal Ideation with Plan', 'Inpatient psychiatric admission for safety and stabilization. Initiate/adjust psychotropic medications. Safety planning. Close monitoring.', 'NKDA', 'Initiated Sertraline, Lorazepam PRN agitation', 'Patient expressed active SI with intent/plan during evaluation', 'Placed on 1:1 observation.'),
('Burn - Third Degree (Full Thickness)', 'Requires surgical excision and skin grafting. Fluid resuscitation (Parkland formula). Pain control. Tetanus booster. Nutritional support. Burn center referral.', 'NKDA', 'IV Fluids (Lactated Ringers), IV Morphine, Tetanus Toxoid', 'Clinical assessment: Eschar, insensate', 'Transfer to specialized burn unit arranged.'),
('Stroke - Hemorrhagic (Intracerebral Hemorrhage)', 'Neurosurgical consultation. Blood pressure control (goal SBP <140-160). Reversal of anticoagulation if applicable. Monitor neurological status closely (ICP monitoring may be needed).', 'Warfarin (Anticoagulated)', 'IV Labetalol drip, Vitamin K IV, FFP transfusion', 'CT Head: Large intraparenchymal hemorrhage with midline shift', 'Patient admitted to Neuro ICU.'),
('Septic Shock', 'Early recognition crucial! Fluid resuscitation (30mL/kg crystalloid). Empiric broad-spectrum IV antibiotics STAT (e.g., Vancomycin + Pip/Tazo). Vasopressors (Norepinephrine first-line) if hypotensive despite fluids. Identify/control source of infection. Monitor lactate.', 'NKDA', 'IV Fluids, IV Vancomycin, IV Piperacillin/Tazobactam, Norepinephrine infusion initiated', 'Lactate elevated, Hypotensive, Febrile, Leukocytosis. Blood cultures pending.', 'Patient admitted to ICU.'),
('Status Epilepticus', 'ABCs. Benzodiazepine STAT (IV Lorazepam or IM Midazolam). Load with second-line AED (Fosphenytoin, Valproic Acid, Levetiracetam). Continuous EEG monitoring if continues. Identify/treat underlying cause.', 'NKDA', 'IV Lorazepam x2 doses, loading Fosphenytoin', 'Patient actively seizing >5 minutes', 'Neurology consulted STAT.'),
('Organophosphate Poisoning', 'Decontamination. Atropine IV (large doses may be needed) until bronchial secretions dry. Pralidoxime (2-PAM) IV to reactivate acetylcholinesterase. Supportive care (airway, ventilation).', 'NKDA', 'Atropine IV bolus/infusion, Pralidoxime IV infusion', 'Clinical diagnosis: SLUDGE symptoms (Salivation, Lacrimation, Urination, Defecation, GI upset, Emesis), miosis, bradycardia after pesticide exposure', 'Toxicology/Poison Control consulted.'),
('Malignant Hyperthermia', 'Discontinue triggering anesthetic agents STAT. Administer Dantrolene IV. Hyperventilate with 100% O2. Active cooling measures. Treat hyperkalemia/acidosis. Monitor vitals, ETCO2, CK, electrolytes.', 'NKDA', 'Dantrolene IV administered', 'Acute hypercarbia, tachycardia, muscle rigidity, fever during anesthesia', 'Anesthesia emergency.'),
('Anaphylaxis', 'Epinephrine IM STAT (0.3-0.5mg adult). Secure airway (intubation if needed). IV fluids. H1/H2 blockers (Diphenhydramine/Famotidine). Corticosteroids (Methylprednisolone). Observe for biphasic reaction.', 'Peanuts (known allergen)', 'Epinephrine IM x1, IV Fluids, IV Diphenhydramine, IV Methylprednisolone', 'Patient developed hives, wheezing, hypotension after accidental peanut ingestion', 'Admitted for observation.'),
('Necrotizing Fasciitis', 'Surgical emergency! Urgent surgical exploration and debridement. Broad-spectrum IV antibiotics (covering Gram pos/neg/anaerobes, e.g., Vancomycin + Pip/Tazo + Clindamycin). Hemodynamic support.', 'NKDA', 'Taken emergently to OR. IV Abx initiated.', 'Clinical suspicion: Pain out of proportion, rapidly spreading erythema/edema, crepitus, systemic toxicity', 'High mortality rate without rapid intervention.'),
('Cardiac Tamponade', 'Emergency pericardiocentesis to drain fluid. IV fluid bolus may temporarily help hemodynamics. Identify/treat underlying cause.', 'NKDA', 'Pericardiocentesis performed STAT', 'Echocardiogram: Large pericardial effusion with RV collapse. Beck triad (hypotension, JVD, muffled heart sounds).', 'Patient hemodynamically improved after drainage.'),
('Tension Pneumothorax', 'Immediate needle decompression in 2nd intercostal space midclavicular line OR 5th ICS anterior axillary line. Follow with chest tube insertion.', 'NKDA', 'Needle decompression performed. Chest tube placed.', 'Clinical diagnosis: Respiratory distress, tracheal deviation, absent breath sounds, hyperresonance, hypotension/JVD', 'Life-threatening emergency.'),
INSERT INTO MedicalRecords (Diagnosis, TreatmentPlan, Allergies, Medications, TestResults, Notes) VALUES
('Pulmonary Embolism - Massive (Hemodynamically Unstable)', 'Thrombolysis (Alteplase) or catheter-directed therapy/surgical embolectomy. Anticoagulation (Heparin infusion initially). Hemodynamic support (fluids, vasopressors).', 'NKDA', 'Alteplase infusion initiated. Heparin drip started post-thrombolysis.', 'CT Angiogram Chest: Large saddle embolus. Patient hypotensive, tachycardic.', 'Admitted to ICU.'),
('Spinal Cord Compression', 'Emergency Neurosurgical consultation. High-dose Dexamethasone IV STAT. Urgent MRI spine to confirm diagnosis and level. Radiation oncology consult if due to metastatic tumor.', 'NKDA', 'IV Dexamethasone 10mg x1, then 4mg Q6H', 'Patient presents with acute back pain, lower extremity weakness, bowel/bladder dysfunction', 'Requires rapid diagnosis and treatment to prevent permanent neurological deficit.'),
('Aortic Dissection - Type A (Ascending)', 'Surgical emergency! Immediate Cardiothoracic Surgery consultation for repair. Control BP aggressively (target SBP 100-120, HR <60) with IV beta-blockers (Labetalol, Esmolol) +/- Nitroprusside.', 'NKDA', 'IV Labetalol drip initiated', 'CT Angiogram Chest: Dissection flap noted in ascending aorta', 'Patient presented with tearing chest pain radiating to back.'),
('Myasthenic Crisis', 'ICU admission. Respiratory support (may require intubation/mechanical ventilation). Hold Pyridostigmine temporarily (to reduce secretions). IVIG or Plasmapheresis treatment.', 'NKDA', 'Intubation performed for respiratory failure. IVIG initiated.', 'Patient with known Myasthenia Gravis presents with severe generalized weakness, dysphagia, respiratory distress', 'Neurology consulted STAT.'),
('Thyroid Storm', 'ICU admission. Beta-blocker (Propranolol) for sympathetic symptoms. Thionamide (PTU preferred initially, then Methimazole). Iodine solution (SSKI or Lugol) after thionamide. Corticosteroids (Hydrocortisone). Supportive care (cooling, fluids).', 'NKDA', 'IV Propranolol, PTU NG tube, SSKI, IV Hydrocortisone', 'Patient presents with high fever, tachycardia, delirium, history of untreated Graves disease', 'Endocrinology consulted STAT.'),
('Acute Angle Closure Glaucoma', 'See Row 300 - Emergency Management.', 'NKDA', 'Topical/Systemic IOP lowering agents, Laser Iridotomy plan', 'IOP > 50mmHg', 'Ophthalmology managing emergently.'),
('Diabetic Ketoacidosis (DKA) - Severe', 'ICU admission. IV Fluids (Normal Saline initially). IV Insulin infusion (regular insulin). Hourly glucose monitoring. Electrolyte replacement (especially Potassium). Monitor anion gap and pH for resolution.', 'NKDA', 'IV Insulin drip, IV NS, Potassium Chloride IV rider added', 'BG >500, pH <7.1, Bicarb <10, Ketones positive, Anion Gap >20', 'Endocrinology consulted.'),
('Hyperosmolar Hyperglycemic State (HHS)', 'ICU admission. Aggressive IV Fluid resuscitation (Normal Saline). IV Insulin infusion (often lower rate than DKA). Electrolyte monitoring/replacement. Identify/treat precipitating cause.', 'NKDA', 'IV NS @ high rate, Low-dose IV Insulin drip', 'BG >800, Serum Osmolality >320, Minimal ketones, Profound dehydration', 'Often occurs in Type 2 DM, high mortality.'),
('Methanol or Ethylene Glycol Poisoning', 'Antidote therapy (Fomepizole IV or Ethanol IV). Correct metabolic acidosis (Sodium Bicarbonate). Hemodialysis may be required to remove toxin and correct acidosis/renal failure.', 'NKDA', 'Fomepizole IV loading dose initiated', 'High anion gap metabolic acidosis, Osmolal gap present, history of ingestion', 'Poison Control/Toxicology consulted.'),
('Carbon Monoxide Poisoning', '100% High-flow oxygen via non-rebreather mask. Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) considered for severe cases (LOC, neuro deficits, cardiac ischemia, pregnant). Monitor Carboxyhemoglobin level.', 'NKDA', '100% O2 via NRB. HBOT consult placed.', 'COHgb level elevated. Patient found in enclosed space with faulty heater.', 'Remove from source exposure!'),
('Cyanide Poisoning', 'Cyanide antidote kit (Amyl Nitrite inhalation, Sodium Nitrite IV, Sodium Thiosulfate IV) OR Hydroxocobalamin IV. 100% Oxygen. Supportive care.', 'NKDA', 'Hydroxocobalamin IV infusion started', 'History of smoke inhalation (fire victim) or industrial exposure with rapid onset LOC, seizures, metabolic acidosis, high lactate', 'Medical emergency.'),
('Heat Stroke', 'Immediate active cooling (ice water immersion preferred, evaporative cooling). Monitor core temperature continuously. Supportive care (fluids, electrolytes). Treat complications (rhabdomyolysis, seizures).', 'NKDA', 'Cooling measures initiated STAT (immersion/wet sheets/fans)', 'Core Temp >40C (104F), Altered mental status, Hot/dry skin (classic) or sweaty (exertional)', 'Stop cooling once core temp reaches ~39C (102.2F).'),
('Hypothermia, Severe', 'Active internal rewarming (warmed IV fluids, warm humidified O2, peritoneal/thoracic lavage) + external warming (forced air blanket). Monitor core temp, EKG (risk of arrhythmias like Osborn waves), electrolytes. Handle gently.', 'NKDA', 'Rewarming protocols initiated. Continuous EKG monitoring.', 'Core Temp <28C (82.4F), Bradycardia, Altered mental status', '"No one is dead until they are warm and dead."'),
('Cauda Equina Syndrome', 'Emergency MRI Lumbar Spine. Urgent Neurosurgical consultation for surgical decompression.', 'NKDA', 'IV Dexamethasone considered. Prepped for emergent surgery.', 'Patient presents with saddle anesthesia, bowel/bladder dysfunction, severe low back pain, bilateral leg weakness', 'Time-sensitive neurological emergency.'),
('Compartment Syndrome - Acute', 'Emergency Fasciotomy required to relieve pressure. Measure compartment pressures if diagnosis uncertain. Remove constricting casts/dressings. Pain control.', 'NKDA', 'Patient taken emergently to OR for fasciotomy.', 'Clinical diagnosis: Pain out of proportion, Pain with passive stretch, Paresthesias, Pallor, Pulselessness (late sign), Paralysis (late sign), Pressure (tense compartment)', 'Common after crush injury or fracture.'),
('Rhabdomyolysis - Severe', 'Aggressive IV Fluid resuscitation (Normal Saline) to maintain high urine output (goal >100-200 mL/hr). Monitor CK levels, electrolytes (esp. Potassium), renal function. Alkalinize urine (Sodium Bicarbonate) sometimes used.', 'NKDA', 'High-rate IV NS infusion. Monitor electrolytes Q4-6H.', 'CK >10,000 U/L, Urine dipstick positive for blood but negative for RBCs (myoglobinuria)', 'Risk of acute kidney injury.'),
('Tumor Lysis Syndrome', 'Prophylaxis/Treatment: Aggressive IV hydration, Allopurinol or Rasburicase. Monitor labs closely (Uric acid, K+, Phos, Ca++, Cr). Treat electrolyte abnormalities urgently. Nephrology consult.', 'NKDA', 'IV hydration, Rasburicase administered', 'High Uric Acid, High K+, High Phos, Low Ca++, AKI after initiation of chemotherapy for high-burden malignancy', 'Oncologic emergency.'),
('Superior Vena Cava (SVC) Syndrome', 'Identify/treat underlying cause (usually malignancy). Elevate head of bed. Supplemental Oxygen. Diuretics for edema. Steroids (Dexamethasone) if tumor related. Radiation therapy or stenting may be needed.', 'NKDA', 'Oxygen via NC, IV Furosemide, IV Dexamethasone', 'Clinical diagnosis: Facial/arm swelling, JVD, chest vein distention. CT Chest shows SVC compression by mass.', 'Oncology/Radiation Oncology consulted.'),
('Air Embolism - Venous or Arterial', 'Place patient in Trendelenburg/Left Lateral Decubitus position (venous). 100% Oxygen. Supportive care. Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy may be considered. Identify/stop source.', 'NKDA', 'Positioned patient appropriately. 100% O2 via NRB.', 'Sudden onset respiratory distress, hypotension, neuro changes after central line manipulation or diving incident', 'Requires high index of suspicion.'),
('Torsades de Pointes', 'IV Magnesium Sulfate STAT. Correct electrolyte abnormalities (K+, Ca++). Discontinue offending QT-prolonging drugs. Overdrive pacing or Isoproterenol may be needed if recurrent.', 'NKDA', 'IV Magnesium Sulfate 2g administered', 'EKG: Polymorphic ventricular tachycardia with sinusoidal waveform', 'Can degenerate to ventricular fibrillation.'),
('Ventricular Fibrillation / Pulseless Ventricular Tachycardia', 'Immediate Defibrillation! CPR. Epinephrine IV/IO. Amiodarone or Lidocaine IV/IO. Identify/treat reversible causes (H T).', 'NKDA', 'Defibrillation x1, CPR resumed, Epinephrine administered', 'EKG: Chaotic ventricular rhythm / Rapid VT without pulse', 'ACLS protocol followed.'),
('Asystole / Pulseless Electrical Activity (PEA)', 'CPR. Epinephrine IV/IO. Identify and treat reversible causes (H T - Hypovolemia, Hypoxia, Hydrogen ion (acidosis), Hypo/Hyperkalemia, Hypothermia; Tension pneumo, Tamponade, Toxins, Thrombosis (pulmonary/coronary)). Not shockable rhythms.', 'NKDA', 'CPR in progress, Epinephrine administered', 'EKG: Flat line / Organized rhythm without pulse', 'ACLS protocol followed.'),
('Hypertensive Emergency with End Organ Damage (e.g., Encephalopathy, Stroke, MI, AKI, Aortic Dissection, Eclampsia)', 'ICU admission. IV antihypertensive agent (e.g., Labetalol, Nicardipine, Nitroprusside - agent choice depends on specific end organ damage). Gradual BP reduction (except in dissection/eclampsia). Monitor end organ function.', 'NKDA', 'IV Nicardipine infusion initiated', 'Severe HTN (e.g., >180/120) WITH signs/symptoms of acute end organ damage', 'Requires careful titration of IV medications.'),
('Eclampsia', 'Magnesium Sulfate IV for seizure prophylaxis/treatment. Antihypertensives (Labetalol, Hydralazine) to control severe BP. Definitive treatment is delivery of fetus/placenta.', 'NKDA', 'Magnesium Sulfate IV loading dose + infusion', 'Patient pregnant/postpartum presents with seizures + signs of preeclampsia (HTN, proteinuria)', 'Obstetric emergency.'),
('Placental Abruption', 'Emergency Obstetric consultation. Continuous fetal monitoring. Maternal stabilization (IV fluids, blood products PRN). Prepare for urgent/emergent delivery (often C-section).', 'NKDA', 'IV Fluids initiated. OR prepared.', 'Pregnant patient presents with painful vaginal bleeding, uterine tenderness/rigidity, fetal distress', 'Risk of maternal hemorrhage and fetal demise.'),
('Uterine Rupture', 'Emergency laparotomy and delivery. Uterine repair or hysterectomy may be necessary. Maternal resuscitation (fluids, blood).', 'NKDA', 'Patient taken emergently to OR', 'Sudden onset severe abdominal pain, loss of fetal station, fetal distress, maternal shock, often in patient with prior uterine scar (VBAC attempt)', 'Catastrophic obstetric emergency.'),
('Amniotic Fluid Embolism', 'Rare, unpredictable emergency. Supportive care: Oxygenation/ventilation, Hemodynamic support (fluids, vasopressors), Coagulopathy management (blood products - FFP, cryo, platelets). Often fatal.', 'NKDA', 'Intubation performed. Massive transfusion protocol initiated.', 'Sudden onset hypoxia, hypotension, coagulopathy, seizures during labor or shortly after delivery', 'Diagnosis of exclusion.'),
('Shoulder Dystocia', 'Obstetric emergency during vaginal delivery. Maneuvers required (McRoberts, suprapubic pressure, rotational maneuvers - Woods screw/Rubin, delivery of posterior arm, Gaskin maneuver). Call for help (NICU, anesthesia).', 'NKDA', 'McRoberts maneuver and suprapubic pressure applied', 'Fetal head delivers but anterior shoulder impacted behind pubic symphysis', 'Risk of fetal brachial plexus injury or hypoxia.'),
('Postpartum Hemorrhage', 'Identify cause (Tone, Trauma, Tissue, Thrombin). Uterine massage, Oxytocin infusion, other uterotonics (Methergine, Hemabate, Misoprostol). Manual removal of placenta if retained. Repair lacerations. Fluid/blood resuscitation. May require D&C, uterine artery embolization, or hysterectomy.', 'NKDA', 'Uterine massage, Oxytocin IV, Methergine IM', 'Excessive bleeding (>500mL vaginal / >1000mL C-section) after delivery. Uterus may be boggy.', 'Obstetric emergency.'),
('Neonatal Resuscitation', 'Initial steps: Warm, dry, stimulate, clear airway PRN. Assess HR/Respirations. Positive pressure ventilation (PPV) if apneic/gasping or HR <100. Chest compressions if HR <60 despite effective PPV. Epinephrine IV/IO if HR remains <60. Naloxone if maternal opioid exposure.', 'NKDA', 'PPV initiated via bag-mask ventilation', 'Neonate born limp, apneic, bradycardic', 'NRP algorithm followed.'),
('Foreign Body Aspiration - Complete Airway Obstruction', 'Conscious: Heimlich maneuver (abdominal thrusts adult/child, back blows/chest thrusts infant). Unconscious: CPR, check mouth for object before breaths. May require laryngoscopy/Magill forceps or surgical airway if unsuccessful.', 'NKDA', 'Heimlich maneuver performed successfully', 'Sudden onset choking, inability to speak/cough/breathe', 'Life-threatening emergency.'),
('Chemical Eye Burn', 'Immediate copious irrigation with Normal Saline or water for at least 15-30 minutes (Morgan lens useful). Check pH, continue irrigation until pH neutral (7.0-7.4). Ophthalmology consultation STAT.', 'NKDA', 'Copious irrigation initiated immediately', 'History of chemical splash to eye. Severe pain, redness, vision change.', 'Alkali burns generally worse than acid burns.'),
('Dental Avulsion (Tooth Knocked Out)', 'Handle tooth by crown only. Gently rinse debris (do not scrub). Attempt reimplantation into socket immediately if possible, have patient bite on gauze. If unable, transport tooth in milk or saline STAT to dentist/ED.', 'NKDA', 'Tooth reimplanted by Dentist within 30 mins', 'History of trauma resulting in tooth loss', 'Time is critical for successful reimplantation.'),
('Near Drowning / Submersion Injury', 'Rescue from water. Basic life support (CPR if needed). Oxygenation/ventilation crucial. Manage hypothermia. Hospital admission for observation (risk of delayed pulmonary edema).', 'NKDA', 'Patient intubated in field. Rewarming measures started.', 'Pulled unresponsive from water', 'Outcome depends on duration and severity of hypoxia.'),
('Snakebite - Venomous', 'Keep patient calm and immobilized. Transport to ED STAT. Identify snake if possible (safely). Antivenom administration is key treatment based on snake type and symptoms. Supportive care.', 'NKDA', 'Antivenom (CroFab) infusion started', 'Patient bitten by rattlesnake. Progressive swelling, pain, ecchymosis at bite site.', 'Do NOT use tourniquets, ice, or incision/suction.'),
('Black Widow Spider Bite', 'Clean bite site. Pain control (opioids often needed). Muscle relaxants (benzodiazepines) for severe muscle cramping/spasms. Antivenom available but reserved for severe cases (risk of hypersensitivity).', 'NKDA', 'Morphine IV PRN pain, Lorazepam IV PRN muscle spasm', 'Patient reports bite followed by severe pain, muscle cramping, abdominal rigidity', 'Supportive care is mainstay.'),
('Brown Recluse Spider Bite', 'Clean bite site. Analgesics. Tetanus update. Monitor for necrotic lesion development (may take days-weeks). Surgical debridement may be needed later if extensive necrosis occurs. Dapsone sometimes used (controversial).', 'Sulfa (avoid Dapsone)', 'Acetaminophen/Codeine PRN pain', 'Initial bite may be minor, followed by central blister, surrounding erythema/ischemia, progressing to necrosis/ulceration', 'Most bites heal without complication.'),
('Bee/Wasp Sting - Allergic Reaction (Not Anaphylaxis)', 'Remove stinger if present (scrape, don risk pulling). Clean area. Cold compress. Oral antihistamine (Diphenhydramine). Topical corticosteroid or Calamine lotion for itching.', 'NKDA', 'Diphenhydramine PO, Hydrocortisone cream topical', 'Localized swelling, redness, itching beyond immediate sting site', 'Monitor for signs of anaphylaxis.'),
('Animal Bite (e.g., Dog, Cat)', 'Copious irrigation and cleaning of wound. Assess need for rabies prophylaxis (based on animal, vaccination status, location). Assess need for tetanus booster. Antibiotic prophylaxis often given (e.g., Amoxicillin/Clavulanate), especially for cat bites or hand wounds. Consider primary closure vs delayed closure/healing by secondary intention based on wound/risk.', 'Penicillin', 'Amoxicillin/Clavulanate PO started. Tetanus booster given.', 'Dog bite wound to forearm, moderate depth', 'Wound irrigated, explored, loosely approximated. Rabies PEP deferred (known vaccinated domestic dog).'),
('Human Bite', 'Copious irrigation and cleaning. Tetanus update. Antibiotic prophylaxis strongly recommended (Amoxicillin/Clavulanate). Assess for injury to underlying structures (tendons, joints). Often left open initially due to high infection risk.', 'NKDA', 'Amoxicillin/Clavulanate PO started', 'Fight bite wound over MCP joint', 'High risk for serious infection.'),
('Frostbite', 'Rapid rewarming in warm water bath (37-39C / 98.6-102.2F) until area is pliable and erythematous. Pain management during rewarming (significant pain). Tetanus update. Avoid rubbing affected area. Protect from refreezing. Assess tissue viability after rewarming.', 'NKDA', 'Warm water immersion rewarming initiated. IV Morphine for pain.', 'Fingers white, hard, insensate after prolonged cold exposure', 'May require long-term wound care or amputation depending on severity.'),
('Electrical Burn / Injury', 'ABCs. Cardiac monitoring (risk of arrhythmias). Fluid resuscitation (often require large volumes). Assess for internal injuries (muscle damage -> rhabdomyolysis). Identify entrance/exit wounds. Tetanus update. Burn center referral often needed.', 'NKDA', 'Continuous EKG monitoring. IV Fluid bolus administered.', 'History of contact with high-voltage source. Entrance/exit wounds noted.', 'Risk of severe internal injury despite minimal external appearance.'),
('Lightning Strike', 'Scene safety first! CPR if needed (reverse triage - prioritize those without pulse/respirations). Cardiac monitoring. Assess for burns, neurological injury, ruptured eardrums, eye injuries. Treat specific injuries.', 'NKDA', 'Patient placed on cardiac monitor. Full trauma assessment performed.', 'Found unresponsive outdoors after thunderstorm', 'Unique injury patterns (Lichtenberg figures).'),
('High Altitude Cerebral Edema (HACE)', 'Immediate descent mandatory! Oxygen administration. Dexamethasone IV/PO/IM. Consider Gamow bag if descent delayed. Supportive care.', 'NKDA', 'Oxygen administered. Descent initiated. IV Dexamethasone given.', 'At high altitude (>10,000 ft), presents with ataxia, altered mental status, severe headache', 'Life-threatening altitude illness.'),
('High Altitude Pulmonary Edema (HAPE)', 'Immediate descent mandatory! Oxygen administration. Nifedipine or Sildenafil may help lower pulmonary artery pressure. Consider Gamow bag.', 'NKDA', 'Oxygen administered. Descent initiated. Nifedipine given.', 'At high altitude, presents with dyspnea at rest, cough (may be frothy/pink), hypoxia, crackles on lung exam', 'Life-threatening altitude illness.'),
('Decompression Sickness ("The Bends")', '100% Oxygen administration. Transport to facility with hyperbaric chamber STAT. Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) is definitive treatment. IV fluids.', 'NKDA', '100% O2 via NRB. Transport to hyperbaric facility arranged.', 'Symptoms (joint pain, neuro deficits, skin mottling, respiratory distress) after rapid ascent from diving', 'Recompression needed.'),
('Barotrauma - Ear/Sinus', 'Analgesics (NSAIDs). Decongestants (Pseudoephedrine) or nasal steroids may help. Avoid diving/flying until resolved. Valsalva maneuver cautiously. May require myringotomy if severe ear barotrauma.', 'NKDA', 'Ibuprofen PRN pain, Pseudoephedrine PO', 'Ear pain, hearing loss, sinus pressure after diving or flying', 'Usually resolves spontaneously.'),
('Marine Envenomation (e.g., Jellyfish Sting)', 'Rinse with seawater (NOT freshwater). Remove tentacles carefully (use gloves, scrape). Apply heat (hot water immersion 40-45C / 104-113F) for pain control (for many species). Vinegar rinse for some species (Box Jellyfish). Pain medication.', 'NKDA', 'Hot water immersion provided pain relief', 'Linear, painful, erythematous rash after contact with jellyfish', 'Treatment varies somewhat by species.'),
('Insect Bite - Local Reaction', 'Clean area. Cold compress. Topical corticosteroid or Calamine lotion for itching. Oral antihistamine PRN.', 'NKDA', 'Hydrocortisone 1% cream topical PRN', 'Localized redness, swelling, itching at bite site', 'Monitor for signs of secondary infection.'),
('Tick Removal', 'Use fine-tipped tweezers to grasp tick close to skin surface. Pull upward with steady, even pressure. Clean bite area. Monitor for rash (Lyme) or other symptoms.', 'NKDA', 'Tick removed intact using tweezers', 'Embedded tick noted during skin check', 'Consider tick identification if possible.');
('Benign Essential Tremor - Refractory', 'Trial of Primidone starting 25mg QHS, titrate slowly. Continue Propranolol. Discuss Deep Brain Stimulation (DBS) option if Primidone fails.', 'NKDA', 'Propranolol LA 60mg daily, Primidone 25mg QHS (starting)', 'Neurological exam confirms action tremor', 'Patient reports Propranolol provides only partial relief, tremor significantly impacts ADLs.'),
('Chronic Migraine', 'Botox injections for migraine prophylaxis every 12 weeks. Continue Sumatriptan PRN rescue. Optimize sleep hygiene. Keep headache diary.', 'NKDA', 'OnabotulinumtoxinA (Botox) injections Q12 weeks, Sumatriptan 100mg PO PRN', 'N/A', 'Patient meets criteria for chronic migraine (>15 headache days/month).'),
('Psoriatic Arthritis - Active', 'Start Adalimumab (Humira) SC every 2 weeks. Continue Methotrexate weekly + Folic Acid. Monitor for infection, LFTs, CBC.', 'Sulfa', 'Adalimumab 40mg SC Q2W, Methotrexate 15mg PO weekly, Folic Acid 1mg daily', 'CRP/ESR elevated, DAPSA score indicates high activity', 'Patient failed adequate trial of Methotrexate monotherapy.'),
('Epilepsy - Focal with Impaired Awareness', 'Increase Levetiracetam dose to 1000mg BID. Discuss Vagal Nerve Stimulator (VNS) if seizures persist despite dose optimization. Reinforce medication adherence.', 'NKDA', 'Levetiracetam 1000mg PO BID (Increased from 750mg)', 'Recent EEG showed focal discharges', 'Patient reports 1-2 breakthrough seizures per month.'),
('Bipolar I Disorder - Euthymic', 'Continue Lithium Carbonate ER, maintain therapeutic level (0.6-1.0 mEq/L). Continue supportive psychotherapy. Monitor renal/thyroid function annually.', 'NKDA', 'Lithium Carbonate ER 450mg PO BID', 'Lithium level 0.8 mEq/L, TSH/BMP WNL', 'Patient reports stable mood, good functioning.'),
('Urge Incontinence - Refractory to Oral Meds', 'Trial of Percutaneous Tibial Nerve Stimulation (PTNS) weekly x 12 weeks. Continue pelvic floor exercises. Discuss Botox bladder injections or sacral neuromodulation if PTNS fails.', 'Oxybutynin (Dry Mouth)', 'None currently (failed Mirabegron)', 'Urodynamic testing confirmed detrusor overactivity', 'Patient seeking non-pharmacologic options.'),
('Avascular Necrosis - Hip', 'Referral to Orthopedics for consideration of core decompression or total hip arthroplasty based on stage/severity.', 'NKDA', 'Oxycodone PRN severe pain', 'MRI Hip: Confirmed AVN of femoral head', 'Patient reports progressive groin pain, limited mobility.'),
('Thrombocytopenia - Immune Thrombocytopenic Purpura (ITP)', 'Prednisone taper initiated. Monitor platelet counts closely. Consider IVIG or Rituximab if refractory or steroid-dependent.', 'NKDA', 'Prednisone 1mg/kg/day initial dose', 'Platelet count 15 K/uL. Bone marrow biopsy consistent with ITP.', 'Hematology managing. Patient advised on bleeding precautions.'),
